title: RTE has 'no plans' to bring back Ireland's biggest TV star after scandal over salary
description: Ireland's national broadcaster RTE says it has no plans to bring back star presenter Ryan Tubridy - after negotiations with the TV host broke down.

title: This star could become one of the most powerful magnets in the universe
description: Astronomers have uncovered a star that appears on course to become one of the strongest magnets in the universe.

title: Thousands evacuated as 'out of control' wildfire burns in Tenerife
description: Thousands of people have been evacuated in Tenerife as firefighters and the army struggle to contain an "out of control" wildfire.

title: What is the 'Pi' COVID variant dubbed 'BA.6' – and should we be worried about it?
description: Another new Omicron variant has got scientists talking.

title: Flash flooding and landslides kill at least 72 in India's Himalayan region
description: At least 72 people have died in India's Himalayan region after days of torrential rain triggered landslides and flash floods.

title: Fake 'beach closed' signs installed in Mallorca to keep tourists away from popular spots
description: Activists in Mallorca have put up fake signs warning of jellyfish and falling rocks to try to keep English-speaking tourists away from popular beaches.

title: Sweden 'averts planned attacks' as terror alert level raised to second highest after Koran burnings
description: Sweden's prime minister says planned attacks against his country have been averted as the security service raised the terror threat level to its second highest.

title: Several dogs die after becoming trapped in flooded day care centre
description: The deaths of several dogs at a day care centre during a flash flood was an "entirely preventable tragedy", a grief-stricken pet owner has said.

title: 'I buried my sister 54 days after she was killed': How mass graves haunt a once thriving capital
description: Once the thriving capital of West Darfur, al Geneina is now nearly deserted.

title: Pig kidney keeps working in human body for over a month
description: A genetically modified pig kidney transplanted into a brain-dead patient over a month ago is still working normally, researchers have found.

title: World's longest rail tunnel will be closed for months after freight train derailed
description: The world's longest rail tunnel has closed for repairs after a freight train derailed - and it is not expected to open for months.

title: Thousands urged to evacuate by road and air as wildfire nears Canada's most northern city
description: Thousands of people are being urged to leave a major city in Canada's Northwest Territories as a huge wildfire approaches.

title: At least 60 migrants feared dead off the coast of Cape Verde after boat capsizes
description: More than 60 people are feared dead after a boat carrying mostly Senegalese migrants capsized off the coast of Cape Verde in the Atlantic Ocean.
